  "prompt": "If ballots were cast by contributing money, who would win the 2016 election?",
  "response": "If ballots were cast by contributing money in the 2016 U.S. presidential election, the winner would be determined by which candidate raised the most funds from individual donors. According to Federal Election Commission (FEC) data, Hillary Clinton outraised Donald Trump in terms of total contributions from individuals.\n\nHere's a breakdown of the funds raised by each candidate from individuals:\n\n1. **Hillary Clinton (D):** Approximately $563.8 million\n2. **Donald Trump (R):** Approximately $333.2 million\n\nBased on these figures, if ballots were cast by contributing money, Hillary Clinton would have won the 2016 election.\n\nIt's important to note, however, that this hypothetical scenario would fundamentally change the nature of democratic elections and could lead to various legal and ethical issues. The current system aims to ensure that each citizen has an equal vote, regardless of their financial means.",
